LXII. On some gardens which required refurnishing. There is no evidence to shew where these gardens were, or to whom they belonged: probably not to Martial: unless this epigram has been shifted out of its proper place, and refers to the horti (ΧΠ. 31) given to him by Marcella in Spain. If we could sup· pose the allusion here to be to his villa at Nomentum it would so far support Brandt's contentiori that Martial bought that villa, and that it was not a present to him (XI. 18).
